The paper proposes a general model for plane-based clustering, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. The paper discusses optimization problems and termination conditions, which are typical topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method also introduces a new loss function to capture data distribution, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses within-cluster and between-cluster losses, which are typical topics in the sub-category of cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the paper presents experimental results to verify the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
